## Authentication Setup

Each client requires these env vars in `~/.exodus/env.local`:

```bash
# dbt Cloud Enterprise — Client Credentials
export DBT_CLOUD_HOST="https://<account>.us1.dbt.com"  # or eu1, au, custom
export DBT_CLOUD_TOKEN="<service-token>"               # dbt Cloud > Account Settings > Service Tokens
export DBT_CLOUD_ACCOUNT_ID="<account-id>"             # URL: cloud.getdbt.com/accounts/<id>
export DBT_CLOUD_PROD_ENV_ID="<prod-env-id>"           # Environments > Production > ID in URL
export DBT_CLOUD_DEV_ENV_ID="<dev-env-id>"             # Environments > Development > ID in URL
```

**Service Token Permissions Required:**
- `Metadata Only` — for Discovery API read access
- `Semantic Layer Only` — for Semantic Layer queries
- `Job Admin` — for triggering and monitoring jobs
- Recommend: create one token per permission type for least-privilege access

