## Semantic Layer — Metric Review Conventions

When reviewing changes that affect metric definitions (`metrics:` in `.yml` files):

```yaml
# Required structure for every metric
metrics:
  - name: revenue                           # snake_case, noun or noun phrase
    label: "Total Revenue"                  # Title Case, for UI display
    description: "Sum of completed order revenue, net of refunds"
    type: simple                            # simple | ratio | derived | cumulative
    type_params:
      measure:
        name: order_revenue
        fill_nulls_with: 0
    filter: |
      {{ Dimension('order__status') }} = 'completed'
    dimensions:
      - name: metric_time
      - name: customer__country
```

**BLOCK if:**
- Metric has no `description`
- Metric references a column that does not exist in the underlying model
- Metric name conflicts with an existing metric

**WARN if:**
- Metric lacks a `label` (UI will show raw snake_case name)
- No `filter` is defined on a metric that should exclude draft/cancelled records

